Reasoning: The paper discusses two important properties in compressed sensing, namely the null space property (NSP) and the restricted isometry property (RIP). These properties are closely related to information theory (cs.IT), signal processing (cs.SP), numerical analysis (cs.NA), machine learning (cs.LG), and mathematical modeling (cs.MM). The paper also presents a constructive result that shows the RIP-NSP is stronger than NSP, which is of interest to researchers in these sub-categories.
